    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The decay of sound energy as its distance from the sound source increases, due to the conversion of the acoustic energy to heat generated in the medium.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000076943/Academic Press Dictionary of Science and Technology (1992)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>El descenso de energía del sonido en la medida que su distancia de la fuente de sonido aumenta, debido a la conversión de la energía acústica a calor generado en el medio.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Het verminderen van geluidsenergie naarmate de afstand ten opzichte van de geluidsbron toeneemt, door omzetting van de akoestische energie in warmte die in het medium wordt gegenereerd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
